  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem Is Captured'
      title: Jerusalem Is Captured
      number: 1
      content: "  Now it came about after the death of Joshua, that the sons (descendants)
        of Israel (Jacob) asked the Lord, \u201CWho shall go up first for us against
        the Canaanites, to fight against them?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CJudah shall go up [first]; behold, I have
        given the land into his hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And [the tribe of the sons of] Judah said to [the tribe of the sons
        of] Simeon his brother, \u201CCome up with me into my allotted territory,
        so that we may fight against the Canaanites; and I likewise will go with
        you into your allotted territory.\u201D So Simeon went with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Judah went up, and the Lord gave the Canaanites and the Perizzites
        into their hand, and they struck down in defeat ten thousand men at Bezek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then they found Adoni-bezek in Bezek and fought against him, and
        they struck down in defeat the Canaanites and the Perizzites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But Adoni-bezek fled; and they pursued him and caught him and cut
        off his thumbs and his big toes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Adoni-bezek said, \u201CSeventy kings with their thumbs and big toes
        cut off used to gather up scraps of food under my table; as I have done [to
        others], so God has repaid me.\u201D So they brought him to Jerusalem, and
        he died there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the sons of Judah fought against [Jebusite] Jerusalem and captured
        it and struck it with the edge of the sword and set the city on fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Afterward the sons of Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites
        who lived in the hill country, in the Negev (South country) and in the lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Capture of Other Cities'
      title: Capture of Other Cities
      number: 10
      content: 'So Judah went against the Canaanites who lived in Hebron (the name
        of Hebron formerly was Kiriath-arba); and they defeated Sheshai and Ahiman
        and Talmai.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From there [the tribe of] Judah went against the inhabitants of Debir
        (the name of Debir formerly was Kiriath-sepher [city of books and scribes]). '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Caleb said, \u201CWhoever attacks Kiriath-sepher and captures
        it, I will even give him my daughter Achsah as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s younger brother, captured
        it; so he gave him his daughter Achsah as a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When she came to Othniel, she persuaded him to [allow her to] ask
        her father [Caleb] for a field. Then she [rode up to Caleb and] dismounted
        from her donkey, and Caleb said to her, \u201CWhat do you want?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "She said to him, \u201CGive me a blessing; since you have given me
        the land of the Negev (South country), give me springs of water, too.\u201D
        So Caleb gave her the upper springs and the lower springs.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The sons of [Jethro] the Kenite, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, went
        up from the City of Palms (Jericho) with the sons of Judah, to the wilderness
        of Judah which is in the Negev (South country) near Arad; and they went and
        lived with the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then [the warriors of the tribe of] Judah went with [the warriors
        of the tribe of] Simeon his brother, and they struck the Canaanites living
        in Zephath and utterly destroyed it. So the city was called Hormah (destruction). '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also [the warriors of] Judah captured Gaza with its territory and
        Ashkelon with its territory and Ekron with its territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The Lord was with Judah, and [the tribe of] Judah took possession
        of the hill country, but they could not dispossess and drive out those inhabiting
        the valley because they had iron chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then they gave Hebron to Caleb, as Moses had said, and he drove out
        from there the three sons of Anak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the sons of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites who inhabited
        Jerusalem; so the Jebusites have lived with the sons of Benjamin in Jerusalem
        to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The house of Joseph also went up against Bethel, and the Lord was
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The house of Joseph spied out Bethel (now the name of the city was
        formerly Luz). '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The spies saw a man coming out of the city and they said to him,
        \u201CPlease show us the entrance to the city and we will treat you kindly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So he showed them the entrance to the city, and they struck the city
        with the edge of the sword, but they let the man and all his family go free. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Places Not Conquered'
      title: Places Not Conquered
      number: 26
      content: 'The man went into the land of the Hittites and built a city and named
        it Luz, which is its name to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But [the tribe of] Manasseh did not take possession of Beth-shean
        and its villages, or Taanach and its villages, or the inhabitants of Dor
        and its villages, or the inhabitants of Ibleam and its villages, or the inhabitants
        of Megiddo and its villages; so the Canaanites remained in that land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'It happened when Israel became strong, that they put the Canaanites
        to forced labor, but they did not drive them out completely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Neither did [the warriors of] Ephraim drive out the Canaanites who
        were living in Gezer; so the Canaanites lived in Gezer among them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '[The warriors of the tribe of] Zebulun did not drive out the inhabitants
        of Kitron or of Nahalol; so the Canaanites lived among them and were put
        to forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '[The warriors of the tribe of] Asher did not drive out the inhabitants
        of Acco, or the inhabitants of Sidon, or of Ahlab, or of Achzib, or of Helbah,
        or of Aphik, or of Rehob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the Asherites lived among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the
        land, because they did not drive them out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Neither did [the warriors of] Naphtali drive out the inhabitants
        of Beth-shemesh, or the inhabitants of Beth-anath, but they lived among the
        Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land; and the inhabitants of Beth-shemesh
        and of Beth-anath became forced labor for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then the Amorites forced the sons of Dan [back] into the hill country,
        for they would not allow them to come down into the valley; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'yet the Amorites persisted in living on Mount Heres (the mountain
        of the sun), in Aijalon, and in Shaalbim; but when the power of the house
        (descendants) of Joseph became strong and prevailed, they became forced labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: The border of the Amorites ran from the ascent of Akrabbim, from Sela
        (rock) and upward.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Rebuked'
      title: Israel Rebuked
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the Angel of the Lord came up from Gilgal to Bochim. And he
        said, \u201CI brought you up from Egypt and led you to the land which I swore
        [to give] to your fathers; and I said, \u2018I will never break My covenant
        with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and as for you, you shall not make a covenant with the inhabitants
        of this land; you shall tear down their altars.\u2019 But you have not obeyed
        Me; what is this that you have done? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I also said, \u2018I will not drive your enemies out before you;
        but they will be like thorns in your sides and their gods will be a snare
        to you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the Angel of the Lord had spoken these words to all the Israelites,
        the people raised their voices and wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Joshua Dies'
      title: Joshua Dies
      number: 5
      content: 'So they named that place Bochim (weepers); and there they offered
        sacrifices to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when Joshua had sent the people away, the [tribes of the] Israelites
        went each to his inheritance, to take possession of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The people served the Lord all the days of Joshua and all the days
        of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had seen all the great work of the
        Lord which He had done for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the Lord, died at the
        age of a hundred and ten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they buried him in the territory of his inheritance in Timnath-heres,
        in the hill country of Ephraim, north of Mount Gaash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Israel Serves Baals'
      title: Israel Serves Baals
      number: 10
      content: 'Also, all [the people of] that generation were gathered to their
        fathers [in death]; and another generation arose after them who did not know
        (recognize, understand) the Lord, nor even the work which He had done for
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the Israelites did evil in the sight of the Lord and worshiped
        and served the Baals, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and they abandoned the Lord, the God of their fathers, who brought
        them out of the land of Egypt. They followed other gods from the gods of
        the peoples who were around them, and they bowed down to them, and offended
        and provoked the Lord to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they abandoned the Lord and served Baal [the pagan god of the
        Canaanites] and the Ashtaroth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the anger of the Lord burned against Israel, and He gave them
        into the hands (power) of plunderers who robbed them; and He sold them into
        the hands of their surrounding enemies, so that they could no longer stand
        [in opposition] before their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Wherever they went, the hand of the Lord was against them for evil
        (misfortune), as the Lord had spoken, and as the Lord had sworn to them,
        so that they were severely distressed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the Lord raised up judges who rescued them from the hands of
        those who robbed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yet they did not listen to their judges, for they played the prostitute
        after other gods and they bowed down to them. They quickly turned aside from
        the way in which their fathers had walked in obeying the commandments of
        the Lord; they did not do as their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When the Lord raised up judges for them, He was with the judge and
        He rescued them from the hand of their enemies all the days of the judge;
        for the Lord was moved to pity by their groaning because of those who oppressed
        and afflicted them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But when the judge died, they turned back and behaved more corruptly
        than their fathers, in following and serving other gods, and bowing down
        to them. They did not abandon their practices or their stubborn ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So the anger of the Lord burned against Israel, and He said, \u201CBecause
        this nation has transgressed (violated) My covenant (binding agreement) which
        I commanded their fathers, and has not listened to My voice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I also will no longer drive out before them any of the nations which
        Joshua left [to be conquered] when he died, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "in order to test [the loyalty of] Israel by them, whether Israel
        will keep the way of the Lord to walk in it, as their fathers did, or not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So the Lord allowed those nations to remain, not driving them out
        at once; and He did not give them into the hand of Joshua.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idolatry Leads to Servitude'
      title: Idolatry Leads to Servitude
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the nations which the Lord left [in order] to test
        Israel by them (that is, all [the people of Israel] who had not [previously]
        experienced any of the wars in Canaan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'only in order that the generations of the sons of Israel might be
        taught war, at least those who had not experienced it previously). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The remaining nations are: the five lords (governors) of the Philistines,
        all the Canaanites, the Sidonians, and the Hivites who lived on Mount Lebanon
        from Mount Baal-hermon to the entrance of Hamath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They were [allowed to remain] for the testing of Israel, to determine
        whether Israel would listen to and obey the commandments of the Lord, which
        He had commanded their fathers (ancestors) through Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the Israelites lived among the Canaanites, Hittites, Amorites,
        Perizzites, Hivites, and Jebusites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and they took their daughters for themselves as wives and gave their
        own daughters to their sons, and served their [pagan] gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the Israelites did evil in the sight of the Lord, and they forgot
        the Lord their God and served the Baals and the Asheroth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The First Judge Rescues Israel'
      title: The First Judge Rescues Israel
      number: 8
      content: 'So the anger of the Lord was kindled against Israel, and He sold
        them into the hand of Cushan-rishathaim king of Mesopotamia; and the Israelites
        served Cushan-rishathaim eight years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But when the Israelites cried out to the Lord [for help], the Lord
        raised up a man to rescue the people of Israel, Othniel the son of Kenaz,
        Caleb\u2019s younger brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Spirit of the Lord came upon him, and he judged Israel. He went
        out to war, and the Lord gave Cushan-rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into
        his hand, and he prevailed over Cushan-rishathaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the land was at rest [from oppression for] forty years. Then
        Othniel the son of Kenaz died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the Israelites again did evil in the sight of the Lord, and the
        Lord strengthened Eglon king of Moab against Israel, since they had done
        what was evil in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Eglon gathered to him the sons of Ammon and Amalek, and went
        and struck down Israel [in defeat], and they took possession of the City
        of Palm Trees (Jericho). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Ehud Rescues Israel from Moab'
      title: Ehud Rescues Israel from Moab
      number: 14
      content: 'And the Israelites served Eglon king of Moab eighteen years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But when the Israelites cried out to the Lord [for help], the Lord
        raised up a man to rescue them, Ehud the son of Gera, a Benjamite, a left-handed
        man. And the Israelites sent a gift of tribute by him to Eglon king of Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Ehud made for himself a sword a cubit long, which had two edges,
        and he bound it on his right thigh under his robe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he brought the tribute to Eglon king of Moab. Now Eglon was a
        very fat man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when Ehud had finished presenting the tribute, he sent away the
        people who had carried it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Ehud himself turned back from the sculptured stones at Gilgal,
        [and he returned to Eglon] and said [to him], \u201CI have a secret message
        for you, O king.\u201D Eglon said \u201CKeep silence.\u201D And all who attended
        him left him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Ehud came to him as he was sitting alone in his [private] cool upper
        chamber, and Ehud said, \u201CI have a message from God for you.\u201D And
        the king got up from his seat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Ehud reached out with his left hand and took the sword from
        his right thigh, and plunged it into Eglon\u2019s belly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the hilt also went in after the blade, and the fat closed over
        the blade, because Ehud did not draw the sword out of his belly; and the
        refuse came out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Ehud went out into the vestibule and shut the doors of the upper
        chamber behind him, and locked them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "When Ehud departed, Eglon\u2019s servants came. And when they saw
        that the doors of the upper room were locked, they said, \u201CHe is only
        relieving himself in the cool room.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'They waited [a very long time] until they became embarrassed and
        uneasy, but he still did not open the doors of the upper room. So [finally]
        they took the key and opened them, and behold, their master had fallen to
        the floor, dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Ehud escaped while they lingered, and he passed beyond the sculptured
        stones and escaped to Seirah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When he had arrived, he blew a trumpet in the hill country of Ephraim;
        and the sons of Israel went down with him from the hill country, and he was
        in front of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CPursue them, for the Lord has handed over
        your enemies the Moabites to you.\u201D So they went down after him and seized
        the fords of the Jordan opposite Moab and did not allow anyone to cross. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They struck down at that time about ten thousand Moabite men, all
        strong, courageous men; not a man escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Shamgar Rescues from Philistines'
      title: Shamgar Rescues from Philistines
      number: 30
      content: 'So Moab was subdued and humbled that day under the hand of Israel,
        and the land was at rest for eighty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: After Ehud came Shamgar the son of Anath, who struck down six hundred
        Philistine men with an oxgoad. He too saved Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Deborah and Barak Rescue from Canaanites'
      title: Deborah and Barak Rescue from Canaanites
      number: 1
      content: '  But the Israelites again did evil in the sight of the Lord, after
        Ehud died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the Lord sold them into the hand of Jabin king of Canaan, who
        reigned in Hazor. The commander of his army was Sisera, who lived in Harosheth-hagoyim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the Israelites cried out to the Lord [for help], for Jabin had
        nine hundred iron chariots and had oppressed and tormented the sons of Israel
        severely for twenty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Deborah, a prophetess, the wife of Lappidoth, was judging Israel
        at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'She used to sit [to hear and decide disputes] under the palm tree
        of Deborah between Ramah and Bethel in the hill country of Ephraim; and the
        Israelites came up to her for judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now she sent word and summoned Barak the son of Abinoam from Kedesh-naphtali,
        and said to him, \u201CBehold, the Lord, the God of Israel, has commanded,
        \u2018Go and march to Mount Tabor, and take with you ten thousand men [of
        war] from the tribes of Naphtali and Zebulun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I will draw out Sisera, the commander of Jabin\u2019s army, with
        his chariots and his infantry to meet you at the river Kishon, and I will
        hand him over to you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Barak said to her, \u201CIf you will go with me, then I will
        go; but if you will not go with me, I will not go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She said, \u201CI will certainly go with you; nevertheless, the journey
        that you are about to take will not be for your honor and glory, because
        the Lord will sell Sisera into the hand of a woman.\u201D Then Deborah got
        up and went with Barak to Kedesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Barak summoned [the fighting men of the tribes of] Zebulun and
        Naphtali to Kedesh, and ten thousand men went up under his command; Deborah
        also went up with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Heber the Kenite had separated himself from the Kenites, from
        the sons of Hobab the father-in-law of Moses, and had pitched his tent as
        far away as the terebinth tree in Zaanannim, which is near Kedesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When someone told Sisera that Barak the son of Abinoam had gone up
        to Mount Tabor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Sisera called together all his chariots, nine hundred iron chariots,
        and all the people who were with him, from Harosheth-hagoyim to the river
        Kishon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Deborah said to Barak, \u201CArise! For this is the day when the
        Lord has given Sisera into your hand. Has the Lord not gone out before you?\u201D
        So Barak went down from Mount Tabor with ten thousand men following him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Lord routed Sisera and all his chariots and [confused] all
        his army with the edge of the sword before Barak; and Sisera dismounted from
        his chariot and fled away on foot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Barak pursued the chariots and the army to Harosheth-hagoyim,
        and the entire army of Sisera fell by the sword; not even one man was left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But Sisera fled on foot to the tent of Jael, the wife of Heber the
        Kenite, because there was peace between Jabin the king of Hazor and the house
        of Heber the Kenite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jael went out to meet Sisera, and said to him, \u201CTurn aside,
        my lord, turn aside to me! Have no fear.\u201D So he turned aside to her
        [and went] into the tent, and she covered him with a rug. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CPlease give me a little water to drink
        because I am thirsty.\u201D And she opened a skin of milk and gave him a
        drink; then she covered him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CStand at the door of the tent, and if any
        man comes and asks you, \u2018Is there anyone here?\u2019 tell him, \u2018No.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Jael, Heber\u2019s wife, took a tent peg and a hammer in her
        hand, and came up quietly to him and drove the peg through his temple, and
        it went through into the ground; for he was sound asleep and exhausted. So
        he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And behold, as Barak pursued Sisera, Jael came out to meet him and
        said to him, \u201CCome, and I will show you the man whom you are seeking.\u201D
        And he entered [her tent] with her, and behold Sisera lay dead with the tent
        peg in his temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So on that day God subdued and humbled Jabin king of Canaan before
        the sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the hand of the sons of Israel pressed down heavier and heavier
        on Jabin king of Canaan, until they had destroyed him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Deborah and Barak'
      title: The Song of Deborah and Barak
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam sang on that day, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CFor the leaders who took the lead in Israel,For the people
        who volunteered [for battle],Bless the Lord!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Hear, O kings; listen, O rulers!I will sing to the Lord,I will sing
        praise to the Lord, the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Lord, when You went out from Seir,When You marched from the field
        of Edom,The earth quaked, the heavens also dripped,Yes, the clouds dripped
        water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The mountains quaked at the presence of the Lord,  Yes, this Sinai,
        at the presence of the Lord, the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIn the days of Shamgar the son of Anath,In the days of Jael,
        the highways were deserted,And travelers went by roundabout ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The villagers ceased to be; they ceased in IsraelUntil I, Deborah,
        arose,Until I arose, a mother in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They chose new gods;Then war was in the gates.Was there a shield
        or spear seenAmong forty thousand in Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My heart goes out to the commanders of Israel,The volunteers among
        the people;Bless the Lord!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Sing of it, you who ride on white donkeys,You who sit on rich carpets,And
        you who walk by the way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'At the sound of those who divide flocks among the watering places,There
        they shall recount the righteous acts of the Lord,The righteous acts toward
        His villagers in Israel.Then the people of the Lord went down to the gates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAwake, awake, Deborah;Awake, awake, sing a song!Arise, Barak,
        and lead away your captives, you son of Abinoam.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then down marched the survivors to the nobles;The people of the Lord
        marched down for Me against the mighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'From Ephraim those whose root is in Amalek came down,After you, Benjamin,
        with your relatives;From Machir came down commanders and rulers,And from
        Zebulun those who handle the scepter of the [office of] scribe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the heads of Issachar came with Deborah;As Issachar, so was Barak;Into
        the valley they rushed at his heels;Among the divisions of ReubenThere were
        great searchings of heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Why [Reuben] did you linger among the sheepfolds,To hear the piping
        for the flocks?Among the divisions of ReubenThere were great searchings of
        heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Gilead remained beyond the Jordan;And why did Dan live as an alien
        on ships?Asher sat [still] on the seacoast,And remained by its landings.[These
        did not come to battle for God\u2019s people.]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But Zebulun was a people who risked their lives to the [point of]
        death;Naphtali also, on the heights of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe kings came and fought;Then the kings of Canaan foughtAt
        Taanach by the waters of Megiddo.Spoils of silver they did not obtain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'From the heavens the stars fought,From their courses they fought
        against Sisera.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The torrent Kishon swept the enemy away,The ancient torrent, the
        torrent Kishon.O my soul, march on with strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the horses\u2019 hoofs beat [loudly]Because of the galloping\u2014the
        galloping of his valiant and powerful steeds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018Curse Meroz,\u2019 said the messenger of the Lord,\u2018Utterly
        curse its inhabitants;Because they did not come to the help of the Lord,To
        the help of the Lord against the mighty.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CMost blessed of women is Jael,The wife of Heber the Kenite;Most
        blessed is she of women in the tent.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Sisera asked for water and she gave him milk;She brought him curds
        in a magnificent bowl.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "She reached out her [left] hand for the tent peg,And her right hand
        for the workmen\u2019s hammer.Then she struck Sisera, she smashed his head;And
        she shattered and pierced his temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He bowed, he fell, he lay [still] at her feet;At her feet he bowed,
        he fell;Where he bowed, there he fell dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201COut of the window she looked down and lamented (cried out in
        a shrill voice),The mother of Sisera through the lattice,\u2018Why is his
        chariot delayed in coming?Why have the hoofbeats of his chariots delayed?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Her wise ladies answered her,Indeed, she repeated her words to herself,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u2018Are they not finding and dividing the spoil?A maiden (concubine)
        or two for every man;A spoil of dyed garments for Sisera,A spoil of dyed
        garments embroidered,Two pieces of dyed garments embroidered for the neck
        of the plunderer?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So let all Your enemies perish, O Lord;But let those who love Him
        be like the rising of the sun in its might.\u201DAnd the land was at rest
        for forty years."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Oppressed by Midian'
      title: Israel Oppressed by Midian
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the Israelites did evil in the sight of the Lord; and the
        Lord gave them into the hand of Midian for seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The [powerful] hand of Midian prevailed against Israel. Because of
        Midian the sons of Israel made for themselves the dens (hideouts) which were
        in the mountains, and the caves and the [mountain] strongholds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For it was whenever Israel had sown [their seed] that the Midianites
        would come up with the Amalekites and the people of the east and go up against
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they would camp against them and destroy the crops of the land
        as far as Gaza, and leave no sustenance in Israel as well as no sheep, ox,
        or donkey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For they would come up with their livestock and their tents, and
        they would come in as numerous as locusts; both they and their camels were
        innumerable. So they came into the land to devastate it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Israel was greatly impoverished because of the Midianites, and
        the Israelites cried out to the Lord [for help].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now it came about when they cried out to the Lord because of Midian, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "that the Lord sent a prophet to the Israelites, and he said to them,
        \u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u2018I brought you up from
        Egypt and brought you out of the house of slavery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I rescued you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand
        of all who oppressed you, and drove them out before you and gave you their
        land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Gideon Is Visited'
      title: Gideon Is Visited
      number: 10
      content: "and I said to you, \u201CI am the Lord your God; you shall not fear
        the gods of the Amorites in whose land you live.\u201D But you have not listened
        to and obeyed My voice.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the Angel of the Lord came and sat under the terebinth tree at
        Ophrah, which belonged to Joash the Abiezrite, and his son Gideon was beating
        wheat in the wine press [instead of the threshing floor] to [hide it and]
        save it from the Midianites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the Angel of the Lord appeared to him and said to him, \u201CThe
        Lord is with you, O brave man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Gideon said to him, \u201CPlease my lord, if the Lord is with
        us, then why has all this happened to us? And where are all His wondrous
        works which our fathers told us about when they said, \u2018Did not the Lord
        bring us up from Egypt?\u2019 But now the Lord has abandoned us and put us
        into the hand of Midian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord turned to him and said, \u201CGo in this strength of yours
        and save Israel from the hand of Midian. Have I not sent you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Gideon said to Him, \u201CPlease Lord, how am I to rescue Israel?
        Behold, my family is the least [significant] in Manasseh, and I am the youngest
        (smallest) in my father\u2019s house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Lord answered him, \u201CI will certainly be with you, and you
        will strike down the Midianites as [if they were only] one man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Gideon replied to Him, \u201CIf I have found any favor in Your sight,
        then show me a sign that it is You who speaks with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Please do not depart from here until I come back to You, and bring
        my offering and place it before You.\u201D And He said, \u201CI will wait
        until you return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Gideon went and prepared a young goat and unleavened bread from
        an ephah of flour. The meat he put in a basket and the broth in a pot, and
        he brought the food to Him under the oak (terebinth) and presented it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The Angel of God said to him, \u201CTake the meat and unleavened
        bread and lay them on this rock, and pour out the broth [over them].\u201D
        And he did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the Angel of the Lord put out the end of the staff that was
        in His hand and touched the meat and the unleavened bread; and fire flared
        up from the rock and consumed the meat and the unleavened bread. Then the
        Angel of the Lord vanished from his sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When Gideon realized [without any doubt] that He was the Angel of
        the Lord, he declared, \u201COh no, Lord God! For now I have seen the Angel
        of the Lord face to face [and I am doomed]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Lord said to him, \u201CPeace to you, do not be afraid; you shall
        not die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Gideon built an altar there to the Lord and named it The Lord
        is Peace. To this day it is still in Ophrah, of the Abiezrites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now on that same night the Lord said to Gideon, \u201CTake your father\u2019s
        bull, the second bull seven years old, and tear down the altar of Baal that
        belongs to your father, and cut down the Asherah that is beside it; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and build an altar to the Lord your God on top of this mountain stronghold
        [with stones laid down] in an orderly way. Then take the second bull and
        offer a burnt sacrifice using the wood of the Asherah which you shall cut
        down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Altar of Baal Destroyed'
      title: The Altar of Baal Destroyed
      number: 27
      content: "Then Gideon took ten men of his servants and did just as the Lord
        had told him; but because he was too afraid of his father\u2019s household
        (relatives) and the men of the city to do it during daylight, he did it at
        night.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Early the next morning when the men of the city got up, they discovered
        that the altar of Baal was torn down, and the Asherah which was beside it
        was cut down, and the second bull was offered on the altar which had been
        built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So they said to one another, \u201CWho has done this thing?\u201D
        When they searched about and inquired, they were told, \u201CGideon the son
        of Joash did it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the men of the city said to Joash, \u201CBring out your son,
        so that he may be executed, because he has torn down the altar of Baal and
        cut down the Asherah which was beside it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But Joash said to all who stood against him, \u201CWill you plead
        for Baal? Will you save him? Whoever pleads for Baal shall be put to death
        while it is still morning. If Baal is a god, let him defend himself, because
        someone has torn down his altar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore on that day he named Gideon Jerubbaal, meaning, \u201CLet
        Baal plead,\u201D because he had torn down his altar.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then all the Midianites and the Amalekites and the people of the
        east assembled together; and they crossed over [the Jordan] and camped in
        the Valley of Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So the Spirit of the Lord  clothed Gideon [and empowered him]; and
        he blew a trumpet, and the Abiezrites were called together [as a militia]
        to follow him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Sign of the Fleece'
      title: Sign of the Fleece
      number: 35
      content: 'He sent messengers throughout [the tribe of] Manasseh, and the fighting
        men were also called together to follow him; and he sent messengers to [the
        tribes of] Asher, Zebulun, and Naphtali, and they came up to meet them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Gideon said to God, \u201CIf You are going to rescue Israel
        through me, as You have spoken, "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "behold, I will put a fleece of [freshly sheared] wool on the threshing
        floor. If there is dew only on the fleece, and it is dry on all the ground
        [around it], then I will know that You will rescue Israel through me, as
        You have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And it was so. When he got up early the next morning and squeezed
        the dew out of the fleece, he wrung from it a bowl full of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Gideon said to God, \u201CDo not let your anger burn against
        me, so that I may speak once more. Please let me make a test once more with
        the fleece; now let only the fleece be dry, and let there be dew on all the
        ground.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: God did so that night; for it was dry only on the fleece, and there
        was dew on all the ground [around it].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Gideon\u2019s 300 Chosen Men"
      title: "Gideon\u2019s 300 Chosen Men"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jerubbaal (that is, Gideon) and all the people who were with
        him got up early and camped beside the spring of Harod; and the camp of Midian
        was north of them by the hill of Moreh in the valley.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then the Lord said to Gideon, \u201CThere are too many people with
        you for Me to hand over Midian to them, otherwise Israel will boast [about
        themselves] against Me, saying, \u2018My own power has rescued me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So now, proclaim in the hearing of the people, \u2018Whoever is afraid
        and trembling, let him turn back and leave Mount Gilead.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        So twenty-two thousand men returned [home], but ten thousand remained.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Lord said to Gideon, \u201CThere are still too many people;
        bring them down to the water and I will test them for you there. Therefore
        it shall be that he of whom I say to you, \u2018This one shall go with you,\u2019
        he shall go with you; but everyone of whom I say to you, \u2018This one shall
        not go with you,\u2019 he shall not go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he brought the people down to the water, and the Lord said to
        Gideon, \u201CYou shall separate everyone who laps the water with his tongue
        as a dog laps, as well as everyone who kneels down to drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now the number of those who lapped [the water], putting their hand
        to their mouth, was three hundred men, but all the rest of the people kneeled
        down to drink water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the Lord told Gideon, \u201CWith the three hundred men who lapped
        I will rescue you, and will hand over the Midianites to you. Let all the
        other people go, each man to his home.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the three hundred men took people\u2019s provisions [for the journey]
        and their trumpets [made of rams\u2019 horns] in their hands. And Gideon
        sent [away] all the other men of Israel, each to his tent, but kept the three
        hundred men. And the camp of Midian was below him in the valley.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now on that same night the Lord said to Gideon, \u201CArise, go down
        against their camp, for I have given it into your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But if you are afraid to go down [by yourself], go with Purah your
        servant down to the camp, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and you will hear what they say; and afterward you will have the
        courage to go down against the camp.\u201D Then he went down with Purah his
        servant to the outposts of the army that was in the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the Midianites and the Amalekites and all the sons of the east
        were lying [camped] in the valley, as countless as locusts; and their camels
        were without number, as numerous as the sand on the seashore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Gideon arrived, there was a man telling a dream to his friend.
        And he said, \u201CListen carefully, I had a dream: there was a loaf of barley
        bread tumbling into the camp of Midian, and it came to the tent and struck
        it so that it fell, and turned it upside down so that the tent lay flat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And his friend replied, \u201CThis [dream] is nothing less than the
        sword of Gideon the son of Joash, a man of Israel. God has given Midian and
        the entire camp into his hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Gideon heard the account of the dream and its interpretation,
        he bowed down in worship. Then he returned to the camp of Israel and said,
        \u201CArise, for the Lord has given the camp of Midian into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He divided the three hundred men into three companies, and he put
        trumpets and empty pitchers into the hands of all of them, with torches inside
        the pitchers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CLook at me, then do likewise. When I come
        to the edge of the camp, do just as I do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Confusion of the Enemy'
      title: Confusion of the Enemy
      number: 18
      content: "When I and all who are with me blow the trumpet (ram\u2019s horn),
        then all around the camp you also blow the trumpets and shout, \u2018For
        the Lord and for Gideon!\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Gideon and the hundred men who were with him came to the edge
        of the camp at the beginning of the middle watch, when the guards had just
        been changed, and they blew the trumpets and smashed the pitchers that were
        in their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When three companies blew the trumpets and broke the pitchers, they
        held the torches in their left hands, and the trumpets in their right hands
        to blow, and they shouted, \u201CA sword for the Lord and for Gideon!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then each stood in his place around the camp; and the entire [Midianite]
        army ran, crying out as they fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When Gideon\u2019s men blew the three hundred trumpets, the Lord
        set the sword of one [Midianite] against another even throughout the whole
        army; and the army fled as far as Beth-shittah toward Zererah, as far as
        the border of Abel-meholah, by Tabbath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The men of Israel were summoned together from [the tribes of] Naphtali
        and Asher and all Manasseh, and they pursued Midian.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Gideon sent messengers throughout the hill country of [the tribe
        of] Ephraim, saying, \u201CCome down against the Midianites and take [control
        of] the waters before them [thereby cutting off the Midianites], as far as
        Beth-barah and the Jordan [River].\u201D So all the men of Ephraim were assembled
        together and they took control of the waters, as far as Beth-barah and the
        Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Then the men of Ephraim took the two leaders of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb,
        and they killed Oreb at the rock of Oreb, and they killed Zeeb at the wine
        press of Zeeb, and pursued Midian; and they brought the heads of Oreb and
        Zeeb to Gideon from across the Jordan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zebah and Zalmunna Routed'
      title: Zebah and Zalmunna Routed
      number: 1
      content: "  And the men of [the tribe of] Ephraim said to Gideon, \u201CWhat
        is this thing that you have done to us, not calling us when you went to fight
        with Midian?\u201D And they quarreled with him vehemently. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But he said to them, \u201CWhat have I done now [that is so significant]
        in comparison with you? Is not the gleaning (leftovers) of the grapes of
        [your tribe of] Ephraim better than the vintage (entire harvest) of [my clan
        of] Abiezer? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "God has given the leaders of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb into your hands;
        and what was I able to do in comparison with you?\u201D Then their anger
        toward him subsided when he made this statement.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Gideon came to the Jordan and crossed over [the river], he and
        the three hundred men who were with him\u2014exhausted, yet [still] pursuing
        [the enemy]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He said to the men of Succoth, \u201CPlease give loaves of bread
        to the people who are following me since they are exhausted, and I am pursuing
        Zebah and Zalmunna, kings of Midian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the leaders of Succoth said, \u201CAre Zebah and Zalmunna already
        in your hands, that we should give bread to your army?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Gideon said, \u201CFor that [response], when the Lord has handed
        over Zebah and Zalmunna to me, I will thrash your bodies with the thorns
        and briars of the wilderness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He went from there up to Penuel and spoke similarly to them; and
        the men of Penuel answered him just as the men of Succoth had answered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Gideon said also to the men of Penuel, \u201CWhen I come again
        in peace, I will tear down this tower.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Zebah and Zalmunna were in Karkor with their armies, about fifteen
        thousand [fighting] men, all who were left of the entire army of the sons
        of the east; for a hundred and twenty thousand swordsmen had fallen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Gideon went up by the route of those who lived in tents to the east
        of Nobah and Jogbehah, and he attacked their camp when the camp was unsuspecting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Zebah and Zalmunna fled, he pursued them and captured the two
        kings of Midian, Zebah and Zalmunna, and terrified the entire army.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Gideon the son of Joash returned from the battle by the ascent
        of Heres. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He captured a young man of Succoth and questioned him. And the youth
        wrote down for him [the names of] the leaders of Succoth and its elders,
        seventy-seven men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He came to the men of Succoth and said, \u201CLook here, Zebah and
        Zalmunna, about whom you taunted me, saying, \u2018Are Zebah and Zalmunna
        now in your hand, that we should give bread to your men who are exhausted?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He took the elders of the city, and thorns of the wilderness and
        briars, and with them he punished the men of Succoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He tore down the tower of Penuel and killed the men of the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Gideon said to Zebah and Zalmunna, \u201CWhat kind of men were
        they whom you killed at Tabor?\u201D And they replied, \u201CThey were like
        you, each one of them resembled the son of a king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He said, \u201CThey were my brothers, the sons of my mother. As the
        Lord lives, if only you had let them live, I would not kill you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So [to humiliate them] Gideon said to Jether his firstborn, \u201CStand
        up, and kill them!\u201D But the youth did not draw his sword, because he
        was afraid, for he was still [just] a boy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Zebah and Zalmunna said, \u201CRise up yourself and strike us;
        for as the man is, so is his strength.\u201D So Gideon arose and killed Zebah
        and Zalmunna, and took the crescent amulets that were on their camels\u2019
        necks.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the men of Israel said to Gideon, \u201CRule [as king] over
        us, both you and your son, also your son\u2019s son, for you have rescued
        us from the hand of Midian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But Gideon said to them, \u201CI will not rule over you, and my son
        will not rule over you; the Lord shall rule over you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Gideon said to them, \u201CI would make a request of you, that
        each one of you give me an earring from his spoil.\u201D For the Midianites
        had gold earrings, because they were Ishmaelites [who customarily wore them]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They answered, \u201CWe will certainly give them to you.\u201D And
        they spread out a garment, and every one of them threw an earring there from
        his spoil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And the weight of the golden earrings that he requested was seventeen
        hundred shekels of gold, apart from the crescent amulets and pendants and
        the purple garments which were worn by the kings of Midian, and apart from
        the chains that were on their camels\u2019 necks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Forty Years of Peace'
      title: Forty Years of Peace
      number: 27
      content: "Gideon made [all the golden earrings into] an ephod [a sacred, high
        priest\u2019s garment], and put it in his city of Ophrah, and all Israel
        worshiped it as an idol there, and it became a trap for Gideon and his household.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Midian was subdued and humbled before the sons of Israel, and
        they no longer lifted up their heads [in pride]. And the land was at rest
        for forty years in the days of Gideon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Jerubbaal (Gideon) the son of Joash went and lived in his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Gideon had seventy sons born to him, because he had many wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And his concubine who was in Shechem also bore him a son, whom he
        named Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Gideon the son of Joash died at a good advanced age and was buried
        in the tomb of Joash his father in Ophrah of the Abiezrites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then it came about, as soon as Gideon was dead, that the Israelites
        again played the prostitute with the Baals, and made Baal-berith their god. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And the Israelites did not remember the Lord their God, who had rescued
        them from the hand of all their enemies on every side; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: nor did they show kindness to the family of Jerubbaal (that is, Gideon)
        in return for all the good that he had done for Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Abimelech\u2019s Conspiracy"
      title: "Abimelech\u2019s Conspiracy"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Abimelech the son of Jerubbaal (Gideon) went to Shechem to
        his mother\u2019s relatives, and said to them and to the whole clan of the
        household of his mother\u2019s father, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak now in the hearing of all the leaders of Shechem, \u2018Which
        is better for you, that seventy men, all of the sons of Jerubbaal rule over
        you, or that one man rule over you?\u2019 Also, remember that I am your own
        bone and flesh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So his mother\u2019s relatives spoke all these words concerning him
        so that all the leaders of Shechem could hear; and their hearts were inclined
        to follow Abimelech, for they said, \u201CHe is our relative.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they gave him seventy pieces of silver from the house of Baal-berith,
        with which Abimelech hired worthless and undisciplined men, and they followed
        (supported) him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he went to his father\u2019s house at Ophrah and murdered his
        brothers the sons of Jerubbaal, seventy men, [in a public execution] on one
        stone. But Jotham the youngest son of Jerubbaal was left alive, because he
        had hidden himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All the men of Shechem and all of Beth-millo assembled together,
        and they went and made Abimelech king, by the oak (terebinth) of the pillar
        (memorial stone) at Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When they told Jotham, he went and stood at the top of Mount Gerizim
        and shouted to them, \u201CHear me, O men of Shechem, so that God may hear
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Once the trees went forth to anoint a king over them, and they said
        to the olive tree, \u2018Reign over us!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the olive tree said to them, \u2018Should I give up my fatness
        by which God and men are honored, and go to wave over the trees?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the trees said to the fig tree, \u2018You come and reign over
        us!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the fig tree said to them, \u2018Should I give up my sweetness
        and my good fruit, and go to wave over the trees?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the trees said to the vine, \u2018You come and reign over us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the vine replied, \u2018Should I give up my new wine, which makes
        God and men happy, and go to wave over the trees?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then all the trees said to the bramble, \u2018You come and reign
        over us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So the bramble said to the trees, \u2018If in truth you are anointing
        me king over you, then come and take refuge in my shade; but if not, let
        fire come out of the bramble and devour the cedars of Lebanon.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CNow then, if you acted in truth and integrity when you made
        Abimelech king, and if you have dealt well with Jerubbaal and his house,
        and have dealt with him as he deserved\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for my father fought for you and risked his life and rescued you
        from the hand of Midian; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "but you have risen against my father\u2019s house today and have
        murdered his sons, seventy men, on one stone, and have made Abimelech, son
        of his maidservant, king over the people of Shechem, because he is your relative\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if then you have acted in truth and integrity with Jerubbaal and
        his house this day, then rejoice in Abimelech, and let him also rejoice in
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But if not, may fire come out from Abimelech and devour the people
        of Shechem and Beth-millo; and may fire come out from the people of Shechem
        and Beth-millo, and devour Abimelech.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Shechem and Abimelech Fall'
      title: Shechem and Abimelech Fall
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Jotham escaped and fled, and went to Beer and lived there because
        of Abimelech his brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Abimelech ruled over Israel for three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then God sent an evil spirit between Abimelech and the leaders of
        Shechem; and the leaders of Shechem acted treacherously against Abimelech, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'so that the violence done to the seventy sons of Jerubbaal (Gideon)
        might come [on the guilty], and that their [innocent] blood might be laid
        on Abimelech their brother, who had killed them, and on the leaders of Shechem,
        who strengthened his hands (encouraged him) to kill his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The leaders of Shechem set men in ambush against Abimelech on the
        mountaintops, and they robbed all who passed by them along the road; and
        it was reported to Abimelech.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Gaal the son of Ebed came with his relatives, and moved into
        Shechem; and the leaders of Shechem trusted him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They went out into the field, gathered the grapes of their vineyard
        and trod them, and held a festival; and they entered the house of their god,
        and they ate and drank, and cursed Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Gaal the son of Ebed said, \u201CWho is Abimelech, and who is Shechem,
        that we should serve him? Is he not [merely] the son of Jerubbaal and is
        Zebul not his lieutenant? Serve the men of Hamor the father (founder) of
        Shechem. Why then should we serve Abimelech? "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "If only this people were under my authority! Then I would remove
        Abimelech and say to him, \u2018Increase [the size of] your army and come
        out [to fight].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When Zebul the ruler of the city heard the words of Gaal the son
        of Ebed, his anger burned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He sent messengers to Abimelech secretly, saying, \u201CBehold, Gaal
        the son of Ebed and his relatives have come to Shechem; and they are stirring
        up the city against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now then, get up during the night, you and the people who are with
        you, and set up an ambush in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then in the morning, at sunrise, you will get up early and rush upon
        and attack the city; and when Gaal and the people who are with him come out
        against you, you shall do to them whatever you can.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Abimelech and all the people who were with him got up during the
        night, and set up an ambush against Shechem, in four companies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Now Gaal the son of Ebed came out and stood in the entrance of the
        city gate; then Abimelech and the people who were with him got up from the
        ambush. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "When Gaal saw the people, he said to Zebul, \u201CLook, people are
        coming down from the mountaintops.\u201D But Zebul said to him, \u201CYou
        are only seeing the shadow of the mountains as if they were men.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Gaal spoke again and said, \u201CLook! People are coming down from
        the highest part of the land, and one company is coming by way of the sorcerers\u2019
        oak tree.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Zebul said to Gaal, \u201CWhere is your [boasting] mouth now,
        you who said, \u2018Who is Abimelech that we should serve him?\u2019 Is this
        not the people whom you despised? Go out now and fight with them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So Gaal went out ahead of the leaders of Shechem and fought with
        Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Abimelech chased him, and he fled before him; and many fell wounded
        as far as the entrance of the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then Abimelech stayed at Arumah, and Zebul drove out Gaal and his
        relatives so that they could not remain in Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The next day the people went out to the field, and it was reported
        to Abimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So he took his people and divided them into three companies, and
        set an ambush in the field; and he looked and saw the people coming out of
        the city. And he rose up against them and struck them down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Then Abimelech and the company with him advanced forward and stood
        in the entrance of the city gate; the two other companies attacked all who
        were in the field and killed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Abimelech fought against the city that entire day. He took the city
        and killed the people who were in it; he demolished the city and sowed it
        with salt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'When all the leaders of the Tower of Shechem heard about it, they
        entered the inner chamber (stronghold) of the temple of El-berith (the god
        of a covenant). '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Abimelech was told that all the leaders of the Tower of Shechem were
        assembled together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "So Abimelech went up to Mount Zalmon, he and all the people with
        him; and Abimelech took an axe in his hand and cut down a branch from the
        trees, picked it up, and laid it on his shoulder. And he said to the people
        with him, \u201CWhat you have seen me do, hurry and do just as I have done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'So everyone of the people also cut down his branch and followed Abimelech,
        and they put the branches on top of the inner chamber and set it on fire
        over those inside, so that all the people in the Tower of Shechem also died,
        about a thousand men and women.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then Abimelech went to Thebez, and camped against Thebez and took
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'But there was a strong (fortified) tower in the center of the city,
        and all the men and women with all the leaders of the city fled to it and
        shut themselves in; and they went up on the roof of the tower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'So Abimelech came to the tower and fought against it, and approached
        the entrance of the tower to burn it down with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "But a certain woman threw an upper millstone [down] on Abimelech\u2019s
        head and crushed his skull. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Then he called quickly to the young man who was his armor bearer,
        and said to him, \u201CDraw your sword and kill me, so that it will not be
        said of me, \u2018A woman killed him.\u2019\u2009\u201D So the young man
        pierced him through, and he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'When the men of Israel saw that Abimelech was dead, each departed
        to his home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'In this way God repaid the wickedness of Abimelech, which he had
        done to his father [Jerubbaal] by killing his seventy brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: Also God repaid all the wickedness of the men of Shechem on their
        heads, and the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal (Gideon) came upon them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Oppression of Philistines and Ammonites'
      title: Oppression of Philistines and Ammonites
      number: 1
      content: '  After Abimelech died, Tola the son of Puah, the son of Dodo, a
        man of Issachar, arose to save Israel; and he lived in Shamir, in the hill
        country of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Tola judged Israel for twenty-three years; then he died and was buried
        in Shamir.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'After him, Jair the Gileadite arose, and he judged Israel for twenty-two
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He had thirty sons who rode on thirty donkeys, and they had thirty
        towns in the land of Gilead that are called Havvoth-jair (towns of Jair)
        to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Jair died and was buried in Kamon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Israelites again did what was evil in the sight of the Lord;
        they served the Baals, the Ashtaroth (female deities), the gods of Aram (Syria),
        the gods of Sidon, the gods of Moab, the gods of the Ammonites, and the gods
        of the Philistines. They abandoned the Lord and did not serve Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the anger of the Lord was kindled against Israel, and He sold
        them into the hands of the Philistines and the Ammonites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and they oppressed and crushed Israel that year. For eighteen years
        they oppressed all the Israelites who were beyond the Jordan in the land
        of the Amorites, which is in Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Ammonites crossed the Jordan to fight against Judah, Benjamin,
        and the house of Ephraim, so that Israel was greatly distressed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the Israelites cried out to the Lord [for help], saying, \u201CWe
        have sinned against You, because we have abandoned (rejected) our God and
        have served the Baals.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord said to the Israelites, \u201CDid I not rescue you from
        the Egyptians, the Amorites, the Ammonites, and the Philistines? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Also when the Sidonians, the Amalekites, and the Maonites oppressed
        and crushed you, you cried out to Me, and I rescued you from their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet you have abandoned (rejected) Me and served other gods; therefore
        I will no longer rescue you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Go, cry out to the gods you have chosen; let them rescue you in your
        time of distress.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Israelites said to the Lord, \u201CWe have sinned, do to us whatever
        seems good to You; only please rescue us this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So they removed the foreign gods from among them and served the Lord;
        and He could bear the misery of Israel no longer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the Ammonites were assembled together and they camped in Gilead.
        And the sons of Israel assembled and camped at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The people, the leaders of Gilead (Israel) said to one another, \u201CWho
        is the man who will begin to fight against the Ammonites? He shall become
        head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jephthah the Ninth Judge'
      title: Jephthah the Ninth Judge
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Jephthah the Gileadite was a brave warrior, but he was the
        son of a prostitute. Gilead was the father of Jephthah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Gilead\u2019s wife bore him sons, and when his wife\u2019s sons grew
        up, they drove Jephthah out and said to him, \u201CYou shall not have an
        inheritance in our father\u2019s house, because you are the son of another
        woman.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jephthah fled from his brothers and lived in the land of Tob;
        and worthless and unprincipled men gathered around Jephthah, and went out
        [on raids] with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it happened after a while that the Ammonites fought against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the Ammonites fought against Israel, the elders of Gilead went
        to get Jephthah from the land of Tob; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and they said to Jephthah, \u201CCome and be our leader, so that
        we may fight against the Ammonites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201CDid you not hate
        me and drive me from the house of my father? Why have you come to me now
        when you are in trouble?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201CThis is why we have
        turned to you now: that you may go with us and fight the Ammonites and become
        head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201CIf you take me back
        [home] to fight against the Ammonites and the Lord gives them over to me,
        will I [really] become your head?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201CThe Lord is the witness
        between us; be assured that we will do as you have said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Jephthah went with the elders of Gilead, and the people made him
        head and leader over them. And Jephthah repeated everything that he had promised
        before the Lord at Mizpah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now Jephthah sent messengers to the king of the Ammonites, saying,
        \u201CWhat is [the problem] between you and me, that you have come against
        me to fight in my land?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The Ammonites\u2019 king replied to the messengers of Jephthah, \u201CIt
        is because Israel took away my land when they came up from Egypt, from the
        [river] Arnon as far as the Jabbok and [east of] the Jordan; so now, return
        those lands peaceably.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But Jephthah sent messengers again to the king of the Ammonites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and they said to him, \u201CThis is what Jephthah says: \u2018Israel
        did not take the land of Moab or the land of the Ammonites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For when they came up from Egypt, Israel walked through the wilderness
        to the Red Sea and came to Kadesh; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "then Israel sent messengers to the king of Edom, saying, \u201CPlease
        let us pass through your land,\u201D but the king of Edom would not listen.
        Also they sent word to the king of Moab, but he would not consent. So Israel
        stayed at Kadesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then they went through the wilderness and went around the land of
        Edom and the land of Moab, and came to the east side of the land of Moab,
        and they camped on the other side of the [river] Arnon; but they did not
        enter the territory of Moab, for the Arnon was the [northern] boundary of
        Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Israel sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, king of
        Heshbon, and Israel said to him, \u201CPlease let us pass through your land
        to our place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Sihon did not trust Israel to pass through his territory; so
        Sihon gathered together all his people and camped at Jahaz and fought against
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Lord, the God of Israel, gave Sihon and all his people into the
        hand of Israel, and they defeated them; so Israel took possession of all
        the land of the Amorites, the inhabitants of that country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They took possession of all the territory of the Amorites, from the
        Arnon as far as the Jabbok, and from the wilderness [westward] as far as
        the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And now the Lord God of Israel has dispossessed and driven out the
        Amorites from before His people Israel, so [why] should you possess it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Do you not possess what Chemosh your god gives you to possess? And
        everything that the Lord our God dispossessed before us, we will possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now are you any better than Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab?
        Did he ever strive against Israel, or did he ever go to war against them? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'While Israel lived in Heshbon and its villages, and in Aroer and
        its villages, and in all the cities along the banks of the Arnon for three
        hundred years, why did you not recover your lost lands during that time? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So I have not sinned against you, but you are doing me wrong by making
        war against me; may the Lord, the [righteous] Judge, judge this day between
        the Israelites and the Ammonites.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Jephthah\u2019s Tragic Vow"
      title: "Jephthah\u2019s Tragic Vow"
      number: 28
      content: 'But the king of the Ammonites disregarded the message of Jephthah,
        which he sent to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon Jephthah, and he passed through
        Gilead and Manasseh, and Mizpah of Gilead, and from Mizpah of Gilead he passed
        on to the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Jephthah made a vow to the Lord and said, \u201CIf You will indeed
        give the Ammonites into my hand, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "then whatever comes out of the doors of my house to meet me when
        I return in peace from the Ammonites, it shall be the Lord\u2019s, and I
        will offer it up as a burnt offering.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then Jephthah crossed over to the Ammonites to fight with them; and
        the Lord gave them into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And from Aroer to the entrance of Minnith he struck them, twenty
        cities, and as far as Abel-keramim (brook by the vineyard), with a very great
        defeat. So the Ammonites were subdued and humbled before the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Jephthah came to his house at Mizpah, and this is what he saw:
        his daughter coming out to meet him with tambourines and with dancing. And
        she was his only child; except for her he had no son or daughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And when he saw her, he tore his clothes [in grief] and said, \u201CAlas,
        my daughter! You have brought me great disaster, and you are the cause of
        ruin to me; for I have made a vow to the Lord, and I cannot take it back.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And she said to him, \u201CMy father, you have made a vow to the
        Lord; do to me as you have vowed, since the Lord has taken vengeance for
        you on your enemies, the Ammonites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And she said to her father, \u201CLet this one thing be done for
        me; let me alone for two months, so that I may go to the mountains and weep
        over my virginity, I and my companions.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And he said, \u201CGo.\u201D So he sent her away for two months;
        and she left with her companions, and wept over her virginity on the mountains. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'At the end of two months she returned to her father, who did to her
        as he had vowed; and she had no relations with a man. It became a custom
        in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: that the daughters of Israel went yearly to tell the story of the
        daughter of Jephthah the Gileadite four days in the year.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jephthah and His Successors'
      title: Jephthah and His Successors
      number: 1
      content: "  The men of [the tribe of] Ephraim were summoned [to action], and
        they crossed over to Zaphon and said to Jephthah, \u201CWhy did you cross
        over to fight with the Ammonites without calling us to go with you? [For
        that] we will burn your house down upon you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jephthah said to them, \u201CMy people and I were in a major
        conflict with the Ammonites, and when I called you [for help], you did not
        rescue me from their hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So when I saw that you were not coming to help me, I took my life
        in my hands and crossed over against the Ammonites, and the Lord handed them
        over to me. So why have you come up to me this day to fight against me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jephthah assembled all the men of Gilead and fought with [the
        tribe of] Ephraim; and the men of Gilead defeated Ephraim, because they had
        said, \u201CYou Gileadites are fugitives of Ephraim, in the midst of [the
        tribes of] Ephraim and Manasseh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Gileadites took the fords of the Jordan opposite the Ephraimites;
        and when any of the fugitives of Ephraim said, \u201CLet me cross over,\u201D
        the men of Gilead would say to him, \u201CAre you an Ephraimite?\u201D If
        he said, \u201CNo,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "they said to him, \u201CThen say \u2018Shibboleth.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        And he said, \u201CSibboleth,\u201D for he could not pronounce it correctly.
        Then they seized him and killed him at the fords of the Jordan. At that time
        forty-two thousand of the Ephraimites fell.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Jephthah judged Israel for six years. Then Jephthah the Gileadite
        died and was buried in one of the cities of Gilead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And after him Ibzan of Bethlehem judged Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He had thirty sons, and thirty daughters whom he gave in marriage
        outside the family, and he brought in thirty daughters [-in-law] from outside
        for his sons. He judged Israel for seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Ibzan died and was buried at Bethlehem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'After him Elon the Zebulunite judged Israel; and he judged Israel
        for ten years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Elon the Zebulunite died and was buried at Aijalon in the land
        of Zebulun.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now after him Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite judged Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He had forty sons and thirty grandsons who rode on seventy donkeys;
        and he judged Israel for eight years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite died and was buried at
        Pirathon in the land of Ephraim, in the hill country of the Amalekites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Philistines Oppress Again'
      title: Philistines Oppress Again
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Israel again did what was evil in the sight of the Lord, and
        the Lord gave them into the hands of the Philistines for forty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And there was a certain man of Zorah, of the family of the Danites,
        whose name was Manoah; and his wife was infertile and had no children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the Angel of the Lord appeared to the woman and said to her,
        \u201CBehold, you are infertile and have no children, but you shall conceive
        and give birth to a son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Therefore, be careful not to drink wine or [any other] intoxicating
        drink, and do not eat anything [ceremonially] unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For behold, you shall conceive and give birth to a son. No razor
        shall come upon his head, for the boy shall be a Nazirite [dedicated] to
        God from birth; and he shall begin to rescue Israel from the hands of the
        Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the woman went and told her husband, saying, \u201CA Man of
        God came to me and his appearance was like the appearance of the Angel of
        God, very awesome. I did not ask Him where he came from, and he did not tell
        me his name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But He said to me, \u2018Behold, you shall conceive and give birth
        to a son, and now you shall not drink wine or [any other] intoxicating drink,
        nor eat anything [ceremonially] unclean, for the boy shall be a Nazirite
        to God from birth to the day of his death.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Manoah pleaded with the Lord and said, \u201CO Lord, please
        let the Man of God whom You sent come again to us and teach us what we are
        to do for the boy who is to be born.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And God listened to the voice of Manoah; and the Angel of God came
        again to the woman as she sat in the field, but Manoah her husband was not
        with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the woman ran quickly and told her husband, \u201CBehold, the
        Man who came to me the other day has appeared to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Manoah got up and followed his wife, and came to the Man and
        said to him, \u201CAre you the Man who spoke to this woman?\u201D He said,
        \u201CI am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Manoah said, \u201CNow when your words come true, what shall
        be the boy\u2019s manner of life, and his vocation?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The Angel of the Lord said to Manoah, \u201CThe woman must pay attention
        to everything that I said to her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "She may not eat anything that comes from the vine nor drink wine
        or [any other] intoxicating drink, nor eat anything [ceremonially] unclean.
        She shall observe everything that I commanded her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Manoah said to the Angel of the Lord, \u201CPlease let us detain
        you and let us prepare a young goat for you [to eat].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Angel of the Lord said to Manoah, \u201CThough you detain me,
        I will not eat your food, but if you prepare a burnt offering, offer it to
        the Lord.\u201D For Manoah did not know that he was the Angel of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Manoah said to the Angel of the Lord, \u201CWhat is your name, so
        that when your words come true, we may honor you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But the Angel of the Lord said to him, \u201CWhy do you ask my name,
        seeing it is wonderful (miraculous)?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Manoah took the young goat with the grain offering and offered
        it on the rock to the Lord, and He performed miracles while Manoah and his
        wife looked on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For when the flame went up toward heaven from the altar, the Angel
        of the Lord ascended in the altar flame. When Manoah and his wife saw this
        they fell on their faces to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Angel of the Lord did not appear again to Manoah or his wife.
        Then Manoah knew that he was the Angel of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Manoah said to his wife, \u201CWe will certainly die, because
        we have seen God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But his [sensible] wife said to him, \u201CIf the Lord had desired
        to kill us, He would not have received a burnt offering and a grain offering
        from our hands, nor would He have shown us all these things, nor would He
        have announced such things as these at this time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the woman [in due time] gave birth to a son and named him Samson;
        and the boy grew and the Lord blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And the Spirit of the Lord began to stir him at times in Mahaneh-dan,
        between Zorah and Eshtaol.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samson\u2019s Marriage"
      title: "Samson\u2019s Marriage"
      number: 1
      content: '  Samson went down to Timnah and at Timnah he saw a woman, one of
        the daughters of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So he went back and told his father and his mother, \u201CI saw a
        woman in Timnah, one of the daughters of the Philistines; now get her for
        me as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But his father and mother said to him, \u201CIs there no woman among
        the daughters of your relatives, or among all our people, that you must go
        to take a wife from the uncircumcised (pagan) Philistines?\u201D And Samson
        said to his father, \u201CGet her for me, because she looks pleasing to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His father and mother did not know that it was of the Lord, and that
        He was seeking an occasion [to take action] against the Philistines. Now
        at that time the Philistines were ruling over Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Samson went down to Timnah with his father and mother [to arrange
        the marriage], and they came as far as the vineyards of Timnah; and suddenly,
        a young lion came roaring toward him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Spirit of the Lord came upon him mightily, and he tore the lion
        apart as one tears apart a young goat, and he had nothing at all in his hand;
        but he did not tell his father or mother what he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So he went down and talked with the woman; and she looked pleasing
        to Samson. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When he returned later to take her, he turned aside to see the carcass
        of the lion; and behold, a swarm of bees and honey were in the body of the
        lion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So he scraped the honey out into his hands and went on, eating as
        he went. When he came to his father and mother, he gave them some, and they
        ate it; but he did not tell them he had taken the honey from the body of
        the lion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His father went down to the woman, and Samson prepared a feast there,
        for that was the customary thing for young men to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Samson\u2019s Riddle"
      title: "Samson\u2019s Riddle"
      number: 11
      content: 'When the people saw him, they brought thirty companions (wedding
        attendants) to be with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Samson said to them, \u201CLet me now ask you a riddle; if you
        can tell me what it is within the seven days of the feast, and solve it,
        then I will give you thirty linen tunics (undergarments) and thirty changes
        of [outer] clothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But if you are unable to tell me [the answer], then you shall give
        me thirty linen tunics (undergarments) and thirty changes of [outer] clothing.\u201D
        And they said to him, \u201CAsk your riddle, so that we may hear it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he said to them,\u201COut of the eater came something to eat,And
        out of the strong came something sweet.\u201DAnd they could not solve the
        riddle in three days.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then on the fourth day they said to Samson\u2019s wife, \u201CPersuade
        your husband to tell us [through you] the [answer to the] riddle, or we will
        burn you and your father\u2019s household with fire. Have you invited us
        to make us poor? Is this not true?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Samson\u2019s wife wept before him and said, \u201CYou only hate
        me, you do not love me; you have asked my countrymen a riddle, and have not
        told [the answer] to me.\u201D And he said to her, \u201CListen, I have not
        told my father or my mother [either], so [why] should I tell you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "However Samson\u2019s wife wept before him seven days while their
        [wedding] feast lasted, and on the seventh day he told her because she pressed
        him so hard. Then she told the [answer to the] riddle to her countrymen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the men of the city said to Samson on the seventh day before sundown,\u201CWhat
        is sweeter than honey?What is stronger than a lion?\u201DAnd he said to them,\u201CIf
        you had not plowed with my heifer,You would not have solved my riddle.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon him mightily, and he went down
        to Ashkelon and killed thirty of them and took their gear, and gave changes
        of clothes to those who had explained the riddle. And his anger burned, and
        he went up to his father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Samson\u2019s wife was given to his companion who had been his
        friend."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samson Burns Philistine Crops'
      title: Samson Burns Philistine Crops
      number: 1
      content: "  But after a while, in the time of wheat harvest, Samson went to
        visit his wife with a young goat [as a gift of reconciliation]; and he said,
        \u201CI will go in to my wife in her room.\u201D But her father would not
        allow him to go in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Her father said, \u201CI really thought you utterly hated her; so
        I gave her to your companion. Is her younger sister not more beautiful than
        she? Please take her [as your wife] instead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Samson said to them, \u201CThis time I shall be blameless in regard
        to the Philistines when I do them harm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Samson went and caught three hundred foxes, and took torches and
        turning the foxes tail to tail, he put a torch between each pair of tails. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When he had set the torches ablaze, he let the foxes go into the
        standing grain of the Philistines, and he burned up the heap of sheaves and
        the standing grain, along with the vineyards and olive groves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Philistines said, \u201CWho did this?\u201D And they were
        told, \u201CSamson, the son-in-law of the Timnite, because he took Samson\u2019s
        wife and gave her to his [chief] companion [at the wedding feast].\u201D
        So the Philistines came up and burned her and her father with fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Samson said to them, \u201CIf this is the way you act, be certain
        that I will take revenge on you, and [only] after that I will stop.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he struck them without mercy, a great slaughter; and he went
        down and lived in the cleft of the rock of Etam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the [army of the] Philistines came up and camped in [the tribal
        territory of] Judah, and overran Lehi (Jawbone). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The men of Judah said, \u201CWhy have you come up against us?\u201D
        And they answered, \u201CWe have come up to bind Samson, in order to do to
        him as he has done to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then three thousand men of Judah went down to the cleft of the rock
        of Etam and said to Samson, \u201CHave you not known that the Philistines
        are rulers over us? What is this that you have done to us?\u201D He said
        to them, \u201CAs they did to me, so I have done to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They said to him, \u201CWe have come down to bind you, so that we
        may hand you over to the Philistines.\u201D And Samson said to them, \u201CSwear
        to me that you will not kill me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CNo, we will [only] bind you securely and
        place you into their hands; but we certainly will not kill you.\u201D So
        they bound him with two new ropes and brought him up from the rock [of Etam].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When he came to Lehi, the Philistines came shouting to meet him.
        And the Spirit of the Lord came upon him mightily, and the ropes on his arms
        were like flax (linen) that had been burned, and his bonds dropped off his
        hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He found a fresh jawbone of a donkey, so he reached out his hand
        and took it and killed a thousand men with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samson said,\u201CWith the jawbone of a donkey,Heaps upon heaps,With
        the jawbone of a donkeyI have struck down a thousand men.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When he finished speaking, he threw the jawbone from his hand; and
        he named that place Ramath-lehi (hill of the jawbone). '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Samson was very thirsty, and he called out to the Lord and said,
        \u201CYou have given this great victory through the hand of Your servant,
        and now am I to die of thirst and fall into the hands of the uncircumcised
        (pagans)?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So God split open the hollow place that was at Lehi, and water came
        out of it. When Samson drank, his spirit (strength) returned and he was revived.
        Therefore he named it En-hakkore (spring which is calling), which is at Lehi
        to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And Samson judged Israel in the days of [occupation by] the Philistines
        for twenty years.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samson\u2019s Weakness"
      title: "Samson\u2019s Weakness"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Samson went to Gaza and saw a prostitute there, and went in
        to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Gazites were told, \u201CSamson has come here.\u201D So they
        surrounded the place and waited all night at the gate of the city to ambush
        him. They kept quiet all night, saying, \u201CIn the morning, when it is
        light, we will kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Samson lay [resting] until midnight, then at midnight he got
        up and took hold of the doors of the city gate and the two door-posts, and
        pulled them up, [security] bar and all, and he put them on his shoulders
        and carried them up to the top of the hill which is opposite Hebron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After this he fell in love with a [Philistine] woman [living] in
        the Valley of Sorek, whose name was Delilah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So the [five] lords (governors) of the Philistines came to her and
        said to her, \u201CPersuade him, and see where his great strength lies and
        [find out] how we may overpower him so that we may bind him to subdue him.
        And each of us will give you eleven hundred pieces of silver.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Delilah said to Samson, \u201CPlease tell me where your great
        strength lies and with what you may be bound and subdued.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Samson said to her, \u201CIf they bind me with seven fresh cords
        (tendons) that have not been dried, then I will be weak and be like any [other]
        man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the Philistine lords brought her seven fresh cords that had
        not been dried, and she bound him with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now she had men lying in ambush in an inner room. And she said to
        him, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D And he broke the cords
        as a string of tow breaks when it touches fire. So [the secret of] his strength
        was not discovered.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Delilah said to Samson, \u201CSee now, you have mocked me and
        told me lies; now please tell me [truthfully] how you may be bound.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said to her, \u201CIf they bind me tightly with new ropes that
        have not been used, then I will become weak and be like any [other] man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Delilah took new ropes and bound him with them and said to him,
        \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D And the men lying in ambush
        were in the inner room. But he snapped the ropes off his arms like [sewing]
        thread.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Delilah said to Samson, \u201CUntil now you have mocked me and
        told me lies; tell me [truthfully] with what you may be bound.\u201D And
        he said to her, \u201CIf you weave the seven braids of my hair with the web
        [and fasten it with a pin, then I will become weak and be like any other
        man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Delilah Extracts His Secret'
      title: Delilah Extracts His Secret
      number: 14
      content: "So while he slept, Delilah took the seven locks (braids) of his hair
        and wove them into the web]. And she fastened it with the pin [of the loom]
        and said to him, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D And he
        awoke from his sleep and pulled out the pin of the [weaver\u2019s] loom and
        the web.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then she said to him, \u201CHow can you say, \u2018I love you,\u2019
        when your heart is not with me? You have mocked me these three times and
        have not told me where your great strength lies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When she pressured him day after day with her words and pleaded with
        him, he was annoyed to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then [finally] he told her everything that was in his heart and said
        to her, \u201CA razor has never been used on my head, for I have been a Nazirite
        to God from my mother\u2019s womb. If I am shaved, then my strength will
        leave me, and I will become weak and be like any [other] man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Delilah realized that he had told her everything in his heart,
        so she sent and called for the Philistine lords, saying, \u201CCome up this
        once, because he has told me everything in his heart.\u201D Then the Philistine
        lords came up to her and brought the money [they had promised] in their hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'She made Samson sleep on her knees, and she called a man and had
        him shave off the seven braids of his head. Then she began to abuse Samson,
        and his strength left him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "She said, \u201CThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201D And he
        awoke from his sleep and said, \u201CI will go out as I have time after time
        and shake myself free.\u201D For Samson did not know that the Lord had departed
        from him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the Philistines seized him and gouged out his eyes; and they
        brought him down to Gaza and bound him with [two] bronze chains; and he was
        forced to be a grinder [of grain into flour at the mill] in the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the hair of his head began to grow again after it had been shaved
        off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now the Philistine lords gathered together to offer a great sacrifice
        to Dagon their god, and to celebrate, for they said,\u201COur god has given
        Samson our enemy into our hands!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "When the people saw Samson, they praised their god, for they said,\u201COur
        god has handed over our enemy to us,The ravager of our country,Who has killed
        many of us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now when they were in high spirits, they said, \u201CCall for Samson,
        so that he may amuse us.\u201D So they called Samson out of the prison, and
        he entertained them. They made him stand between the pillars. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Samson said to the boy who held him by the hand, \u201CLet me
        feel the pillars on which the [roof of the] house rests, so that I may lean
        against them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Samson Is Avenged'
      title: Samson Is Avenged
      number: 27
      content: 'Now the house was full of men and women; all the Philistine lords
        were there, and on the flat roof were about three thousand men and women
        who looked on while Samson was entertaining them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Samson called to the Lord and said, \u201CO Lord God, please
        remember me and please strengthen me just this one time, O God, and let me
        take vengeance on the Philistines for my two eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Samson took hold of the two middle [support] pillars on which the
        house rested, and braced himself against them, one with his right hand and
        the other with his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Samson said, \u201CLet me die with the Philistines!\u201D And
        he stretched out with all his might [collapsing the support pillars], and
        the house fell on the lords and on all the people who were in it. So the
        dead whom he killed at his death were more than those whom he had killed
        during his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then his brothers and his father\u2019s entire [tribal] household
        came down, took him, and brought him up; and they buried him in the tomb
        of Manoah his father, [which was] between Zorah and Eshtaol. So Samson had
        judged Israel for twenty years."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Micah\u2019s Idolatry"
      title: "Micah\u2019s Idolatry"
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a man of the hill country of Ephraim whose name was Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to his mother, \u201CThe eleven hundred pieces of silver
        which were taken from you, about which you cursed [the thief] and also spoke
        about in my hearing, behold, the silver is with me; I took it.\u201D And
        his mother said, \u201CBlessed be my son before the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He returned the eleven hundred pieces of silver to his mother, and
        she said, \u201CI had truly dedicated the silver from my hand to the Lord
        for my son (in his name) to make an image [carved from wood and plated with
        silver] and a cast image [of solid silver]; so now, I will return it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So when he returned the silver to his mother, she took two hundred
        pieces of silver and gave them to the silversmith who made of it an image
        [of silver-plated wood] and a cast image [of solid silver]; and they were
        in the house of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the man Micah had a house of gods (shrine), and he made an ephod
        and teraphim and dedicated and installed one of his sons, who became his
        [personal] priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In those days there was no king in Israel; every man did what was
        right in his own eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now there was a young man from Bethlehem in Judah, from the family
        [of the tribe] of Judah, who was a Levite; and he was staying there [temporarily]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the man left the town of Bethlehem in Judah, to stay wherever
        he could find a place; and as he journeyed, he came to the hill country of
        Ephraim, to the house of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Micah said to him, \u201CWhere do you come from?\u201D And he said
        to him, \u201CI am a Levite from Bethlehem in Judah, and I am going to stay
        wherever I can find a place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Micah said to him, \u201CLive here with me and be a father and
        a [personal] priest to me, and I will give you ten pieces of silver each
        year, a supply of clothing, and your sustenance (room and board).\u201D So
        the Levite went in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Levite agreed to live with the man, and the young man became
        to Micah like one of his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Micah dedicated (installed) the Levite, and the young man became
        his priest and lived in the house of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Micah said, \u201CNow I know that the Lord will favor me and
        make me prosper because I have a Levite as my priest.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Danites Seek Territory'
      title: Danites Seek Territory
      number: 1
      content: '  In those days there was no king in Israel; and in those days the
        tribe of the Danites was seeking an inheritance [of land] for themselves
        to live in, for until then an inheritance had not been allotted to them as
        a possession among the tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the sons of Dan sent from the total number of their [extended]
        family five brave men from Zorah and Eshtaol, to scout the land and to explore
        it; and they said to them, \u201CGo, explore the land.\u201D They came to
        the hill country of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, and lodged there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When they passed near Micah\u2019s house, they recognized the voice
        of the young man, the Levite, and they turned aside there and said to him,
        \u201CWho brought you here? And what are you doing in this place? And what
        do you have here?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CMicah has done this and that for me, and
        he has hired me and I have become his priest.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CPlease ask of God, so that we may know
        whether our journey on which we are going will be successful.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The priest said to them, \u201CGo in peace; the journey on which
        you are going is acceptable to the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the five men went on and came to Laish and saw the people who
        were there, [how they were] living securely in the style of the Sidonians,
        quiet and peaceful; and there was no oppressive magistrate in the land humiliating
        them in anything, and they were far from the Sidonians and had no dealings
        with anyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The five men came back [home] to their brothers at Zorah and Eshtaol,
        and their brothers said to them, \u201CWhat do you have to report?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said, \u201CArise, let us go up against them; for we have seen
        the land, and behold, it is very good (fertile). Will you sit still and do
        nothing? Do not hesitate to go, to enter, to take possession of the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When you enter, you will come to people [feeling] safe and secure
        with a spacious land [widely extended on all sides]; for God has given it
        into your hands\u2014a place where there is no lack of anything that is on
        the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then from the [tribal] family of the Danites, from Zorah and from
        Eshtaol, six hundred men armed with weapons of war set out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They went up and camped at Kiriath-jearim in Judah. Therefore they
        have called that place Mahaneh-dan to this day; it is west of Kiriath-jearim. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Danites Take Micah\u2019s Idols"
      title: "Danites Take Micah\u2019s Idols"
      number: 13
      content: "They went on from there to the hill country of Ephraim and came to
        Micah\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the five men who had gone to scout the country of Laish said
        to their relatives, \u201CDo you know that there are in these houses an ephod,
        teraphim, an image [of silver-plated wood], and a cast image [of solid silver]?
        Now therefore, consider what you should do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they turned in that direction and came to the house of the young
        Levite, at the home of Micah, and asked him how he was doing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now the six hundred men armed with their weapons of war, who were
        of the sons of Dan, stood at the entrance of the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the five men who had gone to scout the land went up and entered
        the house and took the image [of silver-plated wood], the ephod, the teraphim,
        and the cast image [of solid silver], while the priest stood by the entrance
        of the gate with the six hundred men armed with weapons of war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When these [five men] went into Micah\u2019s house and took the [plated]
        image, the ephod, the teraphim, and the cast image, the priest asked them,
        \u201CWhat are you doing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They said to him, \u201CKeep quiet, put your hand over your mouth
        and come with us, and be a father and a priest to us. Is it better for you
        to be a priest to the house of one man, or to be a priest to a tribe and
        family in Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The priest\u2019s heart was glad [to hear that], and he took the
        ephod, the teraphim, and the image, and went among the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So they turned and left, and they put the children, the livestock,
        and the valuables and supplies in front of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When they had gone some distance from the house of Micah, the men
        who were [living] in the houses near Micah\u2019s house assembled [as a militia]
        and overtook the sons of Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They shouted to the Danites, who turned and said to Micah, \u201CWhat
        is your reason for assembling [against us]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He said, \u201CYou have taken away my gods which I have made, and
        the priest, and have gone away; what else do I have left? How can you say
        to me, \u2018What is your reason?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The sons of Dan said to him, \u201CDo not let your voice [of complaint]
        be heard among us, or else angry men will assault you and you will lose your
        life, along with the lives of [everyone in] your household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the Danites went on their way; and Micah saw that they were
        too strong for him, so he turned and went back to his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They took the [idolatrous] things that Micah had made, and his priest,
        and they came to Laish, to a people who were quiet and secure; and they struck
        them with the edge of the sword and burned the city with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And there was no one to rescue them because it was far from Sidon
        and they had no dealings with anyone. It was in the valley which belongs
        to Beth-rehob. And they rebuilt the city and lived in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They named the city Dan, after Dan their forefather who was born
        to Israel (Jacob); however, the original name of the city was Laish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The [tribe of] the sons of Dan set up the image [of silver-plated
        wood] for themselves; and Jonathan the son of Gershom, the son of Moses,
        and his sons were priests to the tribe of the Danites until the day of the
        captivity and exile from the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So they set up for themselves Micah\u2019s [silver-plated wooden]
        image which he had made, and kept it throughout the time that the house (tabernacle)
        of God was at Shiloh."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: A Levite\u2019s Concubine Degraded"
      title: "A Levite\u2019s Concubine Degraded"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened in those days, when there was no king in Israel,
        that a certain Levite living [as an alien] in the most remote part of the
        hill country of Ephraim, who took a concubine for himself from Bethlehem
        in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But his concubine was unfaithful to him, and left him and went to
        her father\u2019s house in Bethlehem of Judah, and stayed there for a period
        of four months. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then her husband arose and went after her to speak kindly and tenderly
        to her in order to bring her back, taking with him his servant and a pair
        of donkeys. So she brought him into her father\u2019s house, and when the
        father of the girl saw him, he was happy to meet him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So his father-in-law, the girl\u2019s father, detained him; and he
        stayed there with him for three days. So they ate and drank, and he lodged
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "On the fourth day they got up early in the morning, and the Levite
        prepared to leave; but the girl\u2019s father said to his son-in-law, \u201CStrengthen
        yourself with a piece of bread, and afterward go your way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So both men sat down and ate and drank together; and the girl\u2019s
        father said to the man, \u201CPlease be willing to spend the night and enjoy
        yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the man got up to leave, but his father-in-law urged him [strongly
        to remain]; so he spent the night there again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "On the fifth day he got up early in the morning to leave, but the
        girl\u2019s father said, \u201CPlease strengthen yourself, and wait until
        the end of the day.\u201D So both of them ate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When the man and his concubine and his servant got up to leave, his
        father-in-law, the girl\u2019s father, said to him, \u201CBehold, now the
        day has drawn to a close; please spend the night. Look, now the day comes
        to an end; spend the night here and celebrate, enjoy yourself. Then tomorrow
        you may get up early for your journey and go home.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the man was not willing to stay the night; so he got up and left
        and came to a place opposite Jebus (that is Jerusalem). With him were two
        saddled donkeys [and his servant] and his concubine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When they were near Jebus, the day was almost gone, and the servant
        said to his master, \u201CPlease come and let us turn aside into this Jebusite
        city and spend the night in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But his master said to him, \u201CWe will not turn aside into a city
        of foreigners who are not of the sons (descendants) of Israel. We will go
        on as far as Gibeah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said to his servant, \u201CCome and let us approach one of
        these places: and we will spend the night in Gibeah or in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So they passed by and went on their way, and the sun set on them
        near Gibeah, which belongs to [the tribe of] Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and they turned aside there to go in and spend the night in Gibeah.
        And the Levite went in and sat down in the open square of the city, because
        no man invited them into his house to spend the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then behold, there was an old man who was coming out of the field
        from his work at evening. He was from the hill country of Ephraim but was
        staying in Gibeah, and the men of the place were sons (descendants) of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When he looked up, he saw the traveler [and his companions] in the
        city square; and the old man said, \u201CWhere are you going, and where do
        you come from?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The Levite replied, \u201CWe are passing through from Bethlehem [in
        the territory] of Judah to the most remote part of the hill country of Ephraim;
        I am from there. I went to Bethlehem of Judah, but I am now going [home]
        to my house, and there is no man [in the city] who will take me into his
        house [for the night]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Yet we have both straw and feed for our donkeys, and also bread and
        wine for me, and for your handmaid, and for the young man who is with your
        servant; there is no lack of anything.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the old man said, \u201CPeace be to you. Only leave all your
        needs to me; and do not spend the night in the open square.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So he brought him into his house and fed the donkeys; and they washed
        their feet and ate and drank.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "While they were celebrating, behold, men of the city, certain worthless
        and evil men, surrounded the house, pounding on the door; and they spoke
        to the master of the house, the old man, saying, \u201CBring out the man
        who came to your house so that we may have relations with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the man, the master of the house, went out and said to them,
        \u201CNo, my fellow citizens, please do not act so wickedly. Since this man
        has come to my house [as my guest], do not commit this sacrilege. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Here is my virgin daughter and this man\u2019s concubine. I will
        bring them out now; abuse and humiliate them and do to them whatever you
        want, but do not commit this act of sacrilege against this man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But the men would not listen to him. So the man took the Levite\u2019s
        concubine and brought her outside to them; and they had relations with her
        and abused her all night until morning; and when daybreak came, they let
        her go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "At daybreak the woman came and collapsed at the door of the man\u2019s
        house where her master was, until it was [fully] light.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When her master got up in the morning and opened the doors of the
        house and went out to go on his way, he saw his concubine lying at the door
        of the house, and her hands were on the threshold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He said to her, \u201CGet up, and let us go.\u201D But there was
        no answer [for she had died]. Then he put her [body] on the donkey; and the
        man left and went home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When he arrived at his house, he took a knife, and taking hold of
        his [dead] concubine, he cut her [corpse] limb by limb into twelve pieces,
        and sent her [body parts] throughout all the territory of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "All who saw the dismembered parts said, \u201CNothing like this has
        ever happened or been seen from the day that the sons of Israel came up from
        the land of Egypt to this day. Consider it, take counsel, and speak [your
        minds]!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Resolve to Punish the Guilty'
      title: Resolve to Punish the Guilty
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the sons of Israel from Dan [in the north] to Beersheba
        [in the south], including the land of Gilead came out, and the congregation
        assembled as one man to the Lord at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The chiefs of all the people of all the tribes of Israel, presented
        themselves in the assembly of the people of God, four hundred thousand men
        on foot who drew the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "(Now the Benjamites [in whose territory the crime was committed]
        heard that the [other tribes of the] sons of Israel had gone up to Mizpah.)
        And the sons of Israel said, \u201CHow did this evil thing happen?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So the Levite, the husband of the woman who was murdered, replied,
        \u201CI had come with my concubine to spend the night in Gibeah, [a town]
        which belongs to [the tribe of] Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the men of Gibeah rose up against me and surrounded the house
        at night because of me. They intended to kill me, but instead they raped
        my concubine [so brutally] that she died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So I took my concubine and cut her [corpse] in pieces and sent her
        [body parts] throughout the land of the inheritance of Israel; for the men
        of Gibeah have committed a lewd and disgraceful act in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now then, all you sons of Israel, all of you, give your advice and
        counsel here [regarding what should be done].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then all the people stood [unified] as one man, saying, \u201CNone
        of us will go to his tent, and none of us will return to his home [until
        this is settled]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But now this is the thing which we will do to Gibeah; we will go
        up by lot against it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and we will take ten men out of a hundred throughout the tribes of
        Israel, and a hundred out of a thousand, and a thousand out of ten thousand
        to bring provisions for the men, so that when they come to Gibeah of Benjamin,
        they may punish them for all the despicable acts which they have committed
        in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So all the men of Israel assembled against the city, united as one
        man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the tribes of Israel sent men through the entire tribe of Benjamin,
        saying, \u201CWhat is this evil thing that has been done among you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now therefore, turn over the men [involved], the worthless and wicked
        men in Gibeah, so that we may put them to death and remove this wickedness
        from Israel.\u201D But the Benjamites would not listen to the voice of their
        brothers, the sons of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the [tribe of the] sons of Benjamin gathered from the cities
        to Gibeah, to go out to battle against the [other] sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Benjamites assembled out of their cities at that time twenty-six
        thousand men who drew the sword, besides the inhabitants of Gibeah, who assembled
        seven hundred chosen men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Out of all these people were seven hundred choice left-handed men;
        each one could sling stones at [a target no wider than] a hair and not miss.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Civil War, Benjamin Defeated'
      title: Civil War, Benjamin Defeated
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the men of Israel, other than Benjamin, assembled four hundred
        thousand men who drew the sword; all of these were men of war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The men of Israel arose and went up to Bethel and asked of God and
        said, \u201CWhich of us shall take the lead to battle against the sons [tribe]
        of Benjamin?\u201D And the Lord said, \u201CJudah [shall go up] first.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the [fighting men of the] sons of Israel arose in the morning
        and camped against Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The men of Israel went out to battle against Benjamin, and assembled
        in battle formation against them at Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Benjamin came out of Gibeah and struck to the ground
        on that day twenty-two thousand [fighting] men of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the people, the [fighting] men of Israel, took courage and strengthened
        themselves and again set their battle line in the same place where they formed
        it the first day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The sons of Israel went up and wept before the Lord until evening,
        and asked of the Lord, \u201CShall we advance again to battle against the
        sons of our brother Benjamin?\u201D And the Lord said, \u201CGo up against
        them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the sons of Israel came against the sons of Benjamin the second
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And [the fighting men from the tribe of] Benjamin went out of Gibeah
        against them the second day and again struck to the ground the sons of Israel,
        eighteen thousand men, all of whom were swordsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then all the sons of Israel and all the people went up and came to
        Bethel and wept; and they sat there before the Lord and fasted that day until
        evening and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the sons of Israel inquired of the Lord (for the ark of the covenant
        of God was there [at Bethel] in those days, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and Phinehas the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron, ministered before
        it in those days), saying, \u201CShall I yet again go out to battle against
        the sons of my brother Benjamin, or shall I quit?\u201D And the Lord said,
        \u201CGo up, for tomorrow I will hand them over to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Israel set men in ambush around Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The [fighting men of the] sons of Israel went up against the sons
        of Benjamin on the third day and placed themselves in battle formation against
        Gibeah as at other times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The Benjamites went out against their army and were lured away from
        the city, and they began to strike and kill some of the people as at other
        times, on the highways, one of which goes up to Bethel and the other to Gibeah,
        and in the open country, about thirty men of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the Benjamites said, \u201CThey are defeated before us, as at
        the first.\u201D But the sons of Israel said, \u201CLet us flee and lure
        them away from the city to the highways.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then all the men of Israel got up from their places and placed themselves
        in battle formation at Baal-tamar; and the men of Israel [who were] in ambush
        rushed from their place in the plain of Maareh-geba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When the ten thousand choice [fighting] men from all Israel came
        against Gibeah, the battle was hard and fierce; but the Benjamites did not
        realize that disaster was about to strike them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the Lord struck down [the tribe of] Benjamin before Israel, so
        that the sons of Israel destroyed twenty-five thousand one hundred men of
        Benjamin that day, all of whom were swordsmen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So the Benjamites realized that they were defeated. Then men of Israel
        gave ground to the Benjamites, because they relied on the men in ambush whom
        they had placed against Gibeah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then the men in ambush quickly rushed and attacked Gibeah; and the
        men in ambush also deployed and struck the entire city with the edge of the
        sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Now the appointed signal between the men of Israel and the men in
        ambush was that they would make a great cloud of smoke rise from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "So the men of Israel turned in the battle, and Benjamin began to
        strike and kill about thirty men of Israel, for they said, \u201CCertainly
        they are defeated before us as in the first battle!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'But when the [signal] cloud began to rise out of the city in a column
        of smoke, the Benjamites looked behind them; and behold, the entire city
        went up in smoke to heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'When the men of Israel turned back again, the men of Benjamin were
        terrified, for they saw that disaster had fallen upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Therefore, they turned their backs before the men of Israel [and
        fled] toward the direction of the wilderness, but the battle followed and
        overtook them. As the [fighting men of the] sons of Benjamin ran among them,
        the Israelites of the cities came out and destroyed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'They surrounded [the men of] Benjamin, pursued them relentlessly,
        and overtook them opposite Gibeah toward the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Thus eighteen thousand men of Benjamin fell, all of these brave and
        able warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The survivors [of Benjamin] turned and fled toward the wilderness
        to the rock of Rimmon, and Israel caught five thousand of them on the roads
        and overtook them at Gidom and killed two thousand of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'So all of Benjamin who fell that day were twenty-five thousand men
        who drew the sword, all of them brave and able warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'But six hundred men turned and fled toward the wilderness to the
        rock of Rimmon and stayed at the rock of Rimmon for four months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: The men of Israel turned back against [the tribe of] the sons of Benjamin
        and struck them with the edge of the sword, both the entire city [of Gibeah]
        and the livestock and all that they found. They also set on fire all the
        [surrounding] towns which they found.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Mourning the Lost Tribe'
      title: Mourning the Lost Tribe
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the men of Israel had sworn [an oath] at Mizpah, \u201CNone
        of us shall give his daughter in marriage to [a man of] Benjamin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the people came to Bethel and sat there before God until evening,
        and lifted up their voices and wept bitterly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said, \u201CO Lord, God of Israel, why has this come about in
        Israel, that there should be today one tribe missing from Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the next day the people got up early and built an altar there
        and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the sons of Israel said, \u201CWhich one from all the tribes
        of Israel did not come up in the assembly to the Lord?\u201D For they had
        taken a great oath concerning him who did not come up to the Lord at Mizpah,
        saying, \u201CHe shall certainly be put to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the sons of Israel felt sorry [and had compassion] for their
        brother Benjamin and said, \u201COne tribe has been cut off from Israel today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Provision for Their Survival'
      title: Provision for Their Survival
      number: 7
      content: "What shall we do for wives for those who are left, since we have
        sworn [an oath] by the Lord that we will not give them any of our daughters
        as wives?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they said, \u201CWhich one is there of the tribes from Israel
        that did not come up to Mizpah to the Lord?\u201D And behold, [it was discovered
        that] no one had come to the camp from Jabesh-gilead, to the assembly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For when the people were assembled, behold, there was not one of
        the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the congregation sent twelve thousand of the most courageous
        men there, and commanded them saying, \u201CGo and strike the inhabitants
        of Jabesh-gilead with the sword, including the women and the children. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And this is the thing that you shall do; you shall utterly destroy
        every male and every woman who is not a virgin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they found among the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead four hundred
        young virgins who had not known a man intimately; and they brought them to
        the camp at Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the whole congregation sent word to the [surviving] sons of
        Benjamin who were at the rock of Rimmon, and proclaimed peace to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So [the survivors of] Benjamin returned at that time, and they gave
        them the women whom they had kept alive from the women of Jabesh-gilead;
        but there were not enough [to provide wives] for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the people were sorry [and had compassion] for [the survivors
        of the tribe of] Benjamin because the Lord had made a gap in the tribes of
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the elders of the congregation said, \u201CWhat shall we do
        for wives for those [men] who are left, since the women of Benjamin have
        been destroyed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They said, \u201CThere must be an inheritance for the survivors of
        Benjamin, so that a tribe will not be wiped out from Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But we cannot give them wives from our daughters.\u201D For the sons
        of Israel had sworn [an oath], \u201CCursed is he who gives a wife to [a
        man from the tribe of] Benjamin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So they said, \u201CListen, there is the yearly feast of the Lord
        at Shiloh, which is on the north side of Bethel, on the east side of the
        highway that goes up from Bethel to Shechem, and on the south side of Lebonah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So they instructed the sons of Benjamin, saying, \u201CGo, set an
        ambush in the vineyards, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and watch; if the daughters of Shiloh come out to dance in the dances,
        then you shall come out of the vineyards and each of you shall catch his
        wife from the daughters of Shiloh, and go to the land of [the tribe of] Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When their fathers or their brothers come to complain to us, we shall
        say to them, \u2018Give them to us voluntarily, because we did not take a
        wife for each man of Benjamin in battle, nor did you give wives to them,
        for that would have made you guilty [of breaking your oath].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the sons of [the tribe of] Benjamin did as instructed and took
        wives according to their number, from the dancers whom they carried away.
        Then they went and returned to their inheritance, and rebuilt the towns and
        lived in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Israel departed from there at that time, each man to
        his tribe and family, and each man went from there to his inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: In those days [when the judges governed] there was no king in Israel;
        every man did what was right in his own eyes.
      comments: []
